name: Blue-ming Beautiful
description:
This lovely blue polish takes my breath away.
It has a slight shimmer to it, and the blue just pops.

This polish got it's cute and fitting name by @katylouseb_nails on Instagram. I was absolutely stuck and couldn't come up with one.
My girls pulled through as always. Thank you Katy!!

The polish dries to a beautiful matte finish. I prefer a top coat.
Photo shows a top coat added.

name: Freaking Envious
description:
What a fitting name for this amazing green thermal with a hint of holo to it.

Darker green when cool, and a neon lime green when warmed.

name: Brash & Sassy
description:
Tangerine orange color with a hint of holo.

This polish dries to a matte finish. I have added a top coat in photo to increase the sass!

name: Sinfully Sweet
description:
A lovely pink with a hint of holo to it.

Gorgeous color.

This dries to a matte finish, but photo shows a top coat to show it's sexy side.

name: Prim & Proper
description:
This is a lovely purple thermal with a hint of holo goodness to it.

When warm, it's a lovely pink.
When cool, a deep royal purple.

name: We'll Never Be Royals
description:
A royal purple jelly polish loaded with different shapes and sizes of glitters.


Gorgeous swatch photos are courtesy of @10cuteicles.

First photo is with no top coat.
Second photo is over one coat of Black Magic Woman.
STUNNING!!

name: Dangle Earrings (silver)
description:
These are lovely little earrings made with my polishes.

I have been able to sleep and shower in mine. I wore my pair for a solid week with no issues. And I have very sensitive ears.

Colors available are listed below. Get them while you can for Christmas presents. 
I will not be restocking these until after the holidays.

name: Dangle Earrings (antique brass)
description: Antique looking earrings made with my polishes.

name: Post Earrings
description:
These are post style earrings made by me with my polishes.

Limited amounts of each color made. I will not be re-ordering supplies until after the holidays.

Colors available are listed below under options.

name: Pendants (silver)
description:
These are little silver pendants made with my polishes to create beautiful jewelry.

Add these to any chain or create a necklace out of these.

name: Tinsletown Nights (topper)
description:
This is a gorgeous clear glitter topper. It is loaded with black, red, white and silver glitters in different shapes and sizes.

Photos courtesy of Dana @10cuteicles on Instagram who does FABULOUS swatches for me!!!

First photo shows one coat over Cult Nails Tempest and Butter by London Pillar Box Red.
GORGEOUS!!!

Second photo shows one coat over a coat of each of the following polishes: Black Magic Woman (pinky), Mid-Life Crisis (ring finger), Cashmere Scarf (middle finger) and Steel Heart (index finger).

name: Mistletoe Kisses
description:
This is a Christmas tree green polish loaded with multiple colored glitters.

Hold your hand over anyone to get your kisses under the Mistletoe.

Photos courtesy of Dana @10cuteicles on Instagram.
Gorgeous photos dear.
Photo shows 2 coats with a top coat.

name: Naughtier than Nice
description:
This is a beautiful red polish loaded with magic square holos that shift from green, blue, yellow and purple with movement.

This beautiful polish would be a great compliment to any of your Christmas events, and would even match your ugly Christmas sweaters.

Photos are courtesy of Dana @10cuteicles on Instagram.
Photos show 3 coats and a top coat.

name: It's Nipply Outside
description:
This is a lovely ice blue sheer based jelly loaded with blue, teal, green and white glitters in various shapes and sizes.

Reminds me of the chilly weather coming our way.

Photos are courtesy of Dana @10cuteicles on Instagram

First three photos show 2 coats with a top coat.
Fourth photo shows one coat over a coat of Blue Satin Chemise.
Fifth photo shows one coat over a coat of Cult Nails Tempest.

Gorgeous either way you look at it!
Grab it while you can, this is a limited Holiday only polish!

name: Holo-day Embraces
description:
This is another Holo polish in a gorgeous a warm cinnamon color.
Absolutely stunning with gorgeous shifting of colors.

Photo courtesy of Dana @10cuteicles on Instagram

Photo shows 2 coats with a top coat.

name: Pine-ing For You
description:
This is a soft forest shade of green with holo. 
The holo on this polish shifts to colors of yellow, orange, green, blue and red.
Very pretty.

Hope you enjoy this one.
Limited Edition, once it's gone....it's gone.

Photos courteous of Dana @10cuteicles on Instagram.

name: Nearly Nude
description:
A gorgeous nude polish with a touch of sheerness to it.

Photos by the lovely Dana @10cuteicles

name: Raging Hormones
description:
This polish is for all those ladies going through what I'm going through.....THE CHANGE!!!

A white creme base with different sizes and shapes of glitters in purple, black and teal. 

Purple for the calm moments when life is going smoothly.
Teal for when things are picking up a bit and maybe getting a little crazy.
Black for when you've just "had it"!

First photo is from the lovely @10cuteicles
Second Photo shows 2 coats and a top coat.

name: Ravishing Rain
description:
I absolutely love purple! Add some glitter to it, and it makes it fabulous!

It's my party and I can cry if I want to. This polish is part of my birthday collection Over 40 & Fabulous!

Photo shows 2 coats with a top coat.

name: 43 & Sexy
description:
This is a light black jellie polish loaded with tons of pink and purple glitters and purple holographic hex glitters, with a touch of silver flair added.

Who says you can't be over forty and sexy?

This photo shows two coats, with a top coat added.

name: Aging Beautifully
description:
This is a beautiful shimmery light purple polish.
Absolutely stunning.

I have on coats with a high gloss top coat for extra shine.
Unfortunately it's a one time polish. Unless I can figure out where the pigment in the unmarked bag came from :(

name: Mid-Life Crisis
description:
A deep gorgeous green polish. 

Photo is courtesy of Dana @10cuteicles on Instagram.

name: Hot Flashes
description:
This color reminds me of what my cheeks look like by the end of the day!
A warm rosy color with a dash of sparkle and shimmer to it.

I have on two coats of this yummy polish with a top coat added. Gorgeous color.

name: Edgy Elephant
description:
My daughter came to play polish the other day. She created another polish for you.
This is a limited edition polish, it will not be re-stocked.

She LOVES elephants. Even has one tattooed on her foot :)

A light grey creme with silver, pink, black and white glitters.
Photo shows 2 coats with a top coat.

First photo is courtesy of Dana @10cuteicles on Instagram.

name: Ms. Ruby's Sweater
description:
A red jellie polish with different glitters in bronze, white and black.

Photo shows 3 coats with a top coat.

name: Campfire Embers
description:
A gorgeous top coat loaded with orange, black, white and bronze glitter.
Photo shows two coats over a light peach base.
Pinky nail is 3 coats, no undie

name: Bluejean Jeggings
description:
A deep blue polish. Beautiful deep color.

Photo is courtesy of @10cuteicles on Instagram.
Lovely swatch!

name: Chocolate Brandy
description:
A gorgeous rich brown.

Photo shows two coats with a top coat.

Pair it with Campfire Embers for a fantastic accent nail.

name: Girl Fight
description:
October is Breast Cancer Awareness Month! Show your support and your love by wearing pink!!

Girl Fight is a soft pink crelly polish with matte pink square glitters in two sizes, Micro glitters, White rectangles and holo circles.

This will be a limited polish. Once I'm out of supplies, it's gone.
You will get a pink awareness ribbon on each bottle. Add a safety pin and you can wear it to show your support!

I have on 2 coats with a top coat applied.

name: Hopelessly Devoted (Thermal)
description:
A thermal polish that changes from a Fuschia when warm to a lavender/purple shade when cool. 

I love the movie Grease!
For some reason, the colors of this polish reminded me of the scene where Olivia Newton John floats her perfume scented stationary into the pool.

First photo shows 2 coats with a top coat at normal state. 
Second photo after running under warm water to heat up my nail.
Third photo is after running under cool water.

name: Moody Judy (Thermal)
description:
A beautiful deep purple thermal that changes to blue when cool.

A little sparkle added to it to given that something extra.

name: Popped Tarts (Reformulated)
description:
A creamy off white crelly polish loaded with glitters in several different shapes, colors and sizes. Lime green, neon yellow, pink, blue, purple and so on!
Reminds me of frosted sprinkled pop tarts.

Photo shows two coats with a top coat.
Second photo is courtesy of @celinedoesnails how cute is it that she added a pop tart to her accent nail!!

name: Juliet
description:
A gorgeous purple jellie polish that dries to a matte finish.

First photo is courtesy of Gaby or @lacqueerloon on Instagram. Gorgeous swatch capturing the beauty of this matte purple.

Second photo shows 2 coats with a top coat added.
Third photo shows 2 accent fingers topped with Forbidden Love glitter top coat.

name: Romeo
description:
A beautiful blue jelly polish that dries to a matte finish. If you don't like matte polishes, don't turn away from this one. Just add a top coat for gorgeous shine that also brightens the color!

First photo is courtesy of @lacquerloon. Thank you so much Gaby for this gorgeous swatch!
Second photo is three coats with no top coat to show the matte finish.
Third photo is with a top coat.

name: Punk Rock Bi-otch (Glows)
description:
This is a white based jellie polish with irridescent glitters, black hex and diamonds and pink skulls.

OH....and it glows silver in the dark. (unfortunately I could not capture with my camera.....)

I remember dressing up as a Punk Rocker girl as a kid

First photo is courtesty of @beginnails 
Photo shows 2 coats over a soft white base coat.
Top coat is applied. I did add a couple perfectly placed skulls for photo purpose. I will say that the skulls are slightly heavy, and though I use a suspension base, they like to sink. Please remember to shake the crap out of it before using!!

name: Angel Eyes
description:
A gorgeous blue holo polish. Color shifts every time you move your fingers.

I have on 2 coats with a top coat.

name: Hollows Eve
description:
This is a black based jellie polish loaded with tons of orange, black and white glitters and white moons.

I have on 3 coats to ensure maximum coverage and glitter capacity!!

name: Black Magic Woman
description:
This is a jet black matte polish. Gorgeous!!

Photo shows 2 coats, completely opaque!

For those of you that don't like matte polish....don't worry. The second photo shows 2 coats, with a top coat added for shine.

Why did I chose this name? I always listen to my #iheartradio app and that just happened to be on while I was taking the photos!

name: Call Me Maybe
description:
This hot pink beauty is a true jellie polish.

First photo I used three coats with a top coat.

Second photo I did an accent finger using two coats of Call Me Maybe, then I dabbed on Burlesque and added another coat of Call Me Maybe and then a top coat.

GORGEOUS!

name: Whut's the Matte-er
description:
This is a bright neon grape color matte polish. It has a lovely shimmer to it.

Wear alone for a matte appearance, or add a top coat to add beautiful shine to this shimmery polish. 

First photo shows two coats with no top coat.
Second photo is with a top coat added.

name: Steel Heart
description:
This is a gorgeous steel colored metallic polish.

I have on two coats with a top coat.
Great night on the town polish :)

Second photo is courtesy of @marnailart. Thank you Marisol.

name: Blue Satin Chemise
description:
This is a soft baby blue metallic polish.

My husband's favorite polishes are the metallics. He thinks there shouldn't be any other types, just metallic.

I have on 2 coats with a high gloss top coat.

name: Kapow Wow
description:
This polish packs a punch!

A bright orange jelly polish that's so bright and eye catching that I had to name it Kapow! One of my favorite terms for bright polishes that you just think "wow" when you see it. So I couldn't stop at just Kapow...
it became Kapow Wow!

I LOVE this one, I hope you do as well.

Second photo shows three coats with a top coat added to add to the wow factor of this color.

name: Kiss My Astroturf
description:
A gorgeous emerald green jelly polish.
Gold, teal and green glitters.

Photo shows three coats for maximum glitter capacity!

name: Forbidden Love (Top Coat)
description:
A beautiful glitter polish. This top coat is packed full of glitters in different shapes, sizes and colors. Stars, moons, hex, bar, etc.

This top coat was made to compliment the star crossed lovers Romeo & Juliet polishes. This top coat took pretty to FABULOUS. Try it over other colors as well.

name: Foxy Lady
description:
This purple is so sexy I had no choice but to name it Foxy Lady.

A lovely crelly polish. 
Photo shows two coats with a top coat applied.
Third Photo is courtesy of @celinedoesnails
